# monet_core component — optional experimental C++ refactor/demo layer.

menu "Monet Core"

config MONET_CPP_EXPERIMENTAL
    bool "Enable experimental C++ wrappers/refactor layer"
    default n
    help
        Compile the optional C++ demonstration layer that lives under
        components/monet_core/src_cpp and include_cpp. It shows how the
        existing C/FreeRTOS architecture maps to embedded-friendly C++
        (RAII LockGuard, RAII CameraFrame, type-safe Queue<T,N>, a Logger
        backend interface, and a MessageBus class with C API wrappers).

        When this is disabled (the default) the firmware builds and runs
        exactly as the stable pure-C path: no C++ source is compiled and
        there is no flash/RAM cost.

        This layer is intentionally a parallel demo. It does NOT replace
        the production msg_bus.c / service_registry.c paths.

if MONET_CPP_EXPERIMENTAL

choice MONET_CPP_LOGGER_BACKEND
    prompt "C++ Logger backend (build-time selection)"
    default MONET_CPP_LOGGER_BACKEND_UART
    help
        Build-time selection of the default Logger backend returned by
        logger_default_backend(). Runtime polymorphism through the
        LoggerBackend interface is still available; this choice only
        picks which concrete backend is wired up by default so we do not
        pay flash for transports we never select.

config MONET_CPP_LOGGER_BACKEND_UART
    bool "UART console backend"

config MONET_CPP_LOGGER_BACKEND_USB
    bool "USB-CDC backend"

endchoice

config MONET_CPP_DEMO_HANG
    bool "Logger demo: deliberately hang a task (exercises the health monitor)"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, the logger demo's worker task stops checking in after a
        few iterations, simulating a wedged task. The TaskHealthMonitor's
        supervisor then reports it as having missed its deadline.

        Left off by default so normal boots never trip the watchdog. The
        worker is intentionally NOT subscribed to the hardware Task Watchdog,
        so even with this on the chip is not reset — only the soft monitor
        logs the offender. (To see a real TWDT reset, set use_wdt=true when
        registering the worker in logger_demo.cpp.)

endif # MONET_CPP_EXPERIMENTAL

endmenu # Monet Core
